Key Match Events: The Magic won the game 106-97 despite the Raptors having their full roster except for RJ Barrett, who was out due to illness.
The Raptors' young players had difficulties against the Magic's defense.
Pre-Game Insights: The Magic were fourth in the East with a strong defense and depth.
The Raptors were on a winning streak but faced a tough challenge from the Magic.
Post-Match Reflections: The Raptors ended a short winning streak with the loss.
The Magic improved their record to 21-15 despite multiple injuries.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cory Joseph had a standout performance with season highs.
Tristan da Silva led the Magic with 25 points.
Caleb Houstan showed promise with effective play.
Jamal Shead and Davion Mitchell competed for minutes as point guards.
